@Node "textfield" "CDpro/Data:Textfield"
@Next "Mark"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc  "Main"
Textfield (text gadgets / string gadgets):

 All string gadgets you can select with the keyboard (use the underlined
 character...).

 - Artist:    artist / group / singer...
 - CD-Title:  name of the CD
 - Label:     label / production number of the CD (like Mute INT 846.888)
 - Year:      production year
 - Land:      production land
 - Tracks:    number of  tracks/titles
 - Time/Size: play time/size of the CD (e.g. Audio-CD: 12:23 or CD-ROM: 655 MB)
 - Format:    data medium, e.g. Maxi-CD / Photo-CD...
 - Style:     style of the tracks, e.g. Audio-CD:Soul, Video-CD:Action
 - Quantity:  number of CDs you have in stock
 - Code:      order number
 - Price:     price of this CD, like "34.00 DM"
 - Comment:   description or what you want...

 Change BUFFER (listview on the rigth border of the main window) for each
 string gadget with the keyboard. Press the SHIFT button and the underlined
 character from the string gadget if the string gadget is not active or
 press the HELP button if your string gadget is active.
@EndNode
@Node "Mark" "CDpro/Data:Mark..."
@Next "leaf"
@Prev "textfield"
@Toc  "Main"

- Mark:       Select the gadget to mark the item.
              You can view / print / search / export marked items...

@EndNode

@Node "leaf" "CDpro/Data:Leaf..."
@Next "Status"
@Prev "Mark"
@Toc  "Main"
With the gadgets "|<","<<","<","number of item",">",">>",">|" you can leaf
the items.

- "|<":        jump to the first item

  Keyboard:    "Cursor up"

- "<<":        jump with jump width=value (menu Prefs:Jump Width)
               to the left

               Default: 5

  Keyboard:    "SHIFT+ Cursor Left"

- "<":         jump an entry to the left

  Keyboard:    "Cursor Left"

- number of    shows the topical item number; select the gadget and insert
  item:        the number of an item you want and press RETURN.

  Keyboard:    LCOMMAND + G  (Menu Data:Go To Number)

- ">":         jump an entry to the right

  Keyboard:    "Cursor Right"

- ">>":        jump with jump width=value (menu Prefs:Jump Width)
               to the right

               Default: 5

  Keyboard:    "SHIFT+ Cursor Right"

- ">|":        jump to the last item

  Keyboard:   "Cursor down"

@EndNode
@Node "Status" "CDpro/Status:Messages..."
@Next "Buffer"
@Prev "leaf"
@Toc  "Main"


Status:    There you can find messages to your last action, bugs...

           This is an interesting help for you.
@EndNode
@Node "buffer" "CDpro/Buffer:Copy/Sort/Remove/New"
@Next "Main"
@Prev "Status"
@Toc  "Main"

- Listview:   You can scroll the listview with the mouse and with the keyboard.
              Press U and SHIFT + U to scroll the listview up/down and press
              a key from "1","2" to "0" to choose an entry it take over the
              entry to the textfield.

- Copy:       Copy the string from the textfield to the accompanying buffer

              (Keyboard: O)

- Sort:       Sort the entries in the listview (topical buffer).

              (Keyboard: R)

- Remove:     Delete some entries from the topical buffer.

              First select the gadget "Remove". Choose the enties you want to
              delete and press ESC at the and.

              (Keyboard: V)

- New:        Delete all entries from the topical buffer

              (Keyboard: N)
@EndNode
@Node "project" "CDpro/Menu:Project..."
@Next "view"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc  "Main"




- New:        New project (clear all items)

- Load:       Select a CDpro file to load (filerequester).

- Save:       Save data to last selected file.

- Save as:    Save data to selected file (filerequester)

- Copyright:  Requester incl. UserID/Username

- Iconify:    Sleepmode,

               using Prefs:Iconify/AppIcon:

                close mainwindow and build appicon called "CDpro" on the
                Workbench-Screen. Doubleclick to return.

               using Prefs:Iconify/AppItem:

                close mainwindow and add "CDpro" to workbench menu "Tools"
                choose the menu item to return.

- Quit:       Finish CDpro
@EndNode
@Node "View" "CDpro/Data:View"
@Next "ds"
@Prev "project"
@Toc  "Main"


- View:      list your data...

              With the menu Prefs:View/Print/Export you can limit the
              items you want to show...

              example 1: If "All" from the menu Prefs:View/Print/Export is
                         active you can see all items...

              example 2: If "Marked Items" from the menu Prefs:View/Print/Export
                         is active you can see all marked items...

              example 3: If something is active from "Artist" to "Comment"
                         (menu Prefs:View/Print/Export) you can limit
                         the items with the following requester.

                         (Insert "d#?" in the requester (e.g. "Artist" is active)
                          you get all artists with "d")

              example 4: If "From/To" from the menu Prefs:View/Print/Export
                         is active insert start/end item number in the following
                         requesters.




           See also the help requester in the menu "Data:Help"...
@EndNode
@Node "ds" "CDpro/Data:Sort / Search..."
@Next "Print"
@Prev "View"
@Toc  "Main"

- Search:              choose your search area in the menu "Prefs:Search"
                       first, then start the search...

- Sort:                choose your sort criterion in the menu "Prefs:Sort"
                       first (upwards / downwards  ...)

- Delete All Items:    delete all items from your list(new list)

- Delete Topcial Item: delete the topical item...

- Delete Marked Items: delete all marked items...

- Reset Marks:         clear all marks .

- Rotate Marks:        marked items <--> not marked

- Go To Number:        Jump to your item number...

                       Insert your item number to the integer gadget in the
                       main window which is now selected and press return...

- Clear Field:         clear the textfield

- Revoke Item:         revoke textfield to last the copied item...

- Copy Item:           copy textfield to the data list

                       It is possible to copy the item automatically.
                       (see menu "Prefs:Copy Item")
@EndNode
@Node "Print" "CDpro/Print"
@Next "Prefs"
@Prev "ds"
@Toc  "Main"





- Normal List:    prints the standard list,
                  limited by the menus Prefs:View/Print/Export,
                                       Prefs:Print/Export

                  for details: help requester in the menu "Print:Help"

- Topical Field:  prints topical field, see also "Normal List"

- List 0-9:       a lot of possibilities for printing your data

                  for details: "Print:Describe The Lists"
@EndNode
@Node "Prefs" "CDpro/Prefs"
@Next "buffermenu"
@Prev "print"
@Toc  "Main"
- View/Print/Export: limit/choose your data for view/print/export...

                     "From Topical Item" means to view/print/export
                     the data from the topical item in the "Data" area
                     of the main window or not.

                     (see also @{" View " Link "View"} for examples.)

- Search:            choose your search area in this menu.
                     If "Forwards" is active the search works forwards
                     otherwise backwards...

- Sort:              choose your sort criterion in this menu and the
                     sort direction ("Upwards" or downwards)...

- Print/Export:      choose the data you want to print/export
                     ("Artist" to "Comment")...

           NLQ:      near letter quality or draft

      1.8 Inch:      Space between 2 lines (1.8 " or 1.6 ")

  Pagenumber:        prints the pagenumber on each page

                     ATTENTION: you need 2 lines for this option, please
                                check/change "Prefs:Print/Export/Page Length"

  Change Headline:   If you print/export the lists 2-7,9 and using
                     wildcard characters in your search word you can change
                     the headline if you want.

  Ask before...      Ask before printing next page.
                     If you have a good printer e.g. laser printer you love
                     this option...

  Ask Printer Ready: Before printing the first page of each printer job
                     CDpro ask you if the printer is ready...

  Page Length:       Number of lines per page...

  Left Margin:       left margin...

- Copy Item:         have an effect on menu "Data:Copy Item"

   Automatically:    copy the textfield (if the field is not free) to the
                     list if you press Return/Enter on your last (not skiped)
                     string gadget (text gadget)...


   Activates Next    If "Prefs:Copy Item/Automatically" is active Return/
   Field:            Enter (see above) copies the textfield to the list and
                     select the first string gadget which you don`t skip...


- Jump Width:        jump with a number of entries to the left/right if you
                     leaf with ">>"/"<<" ...


- Buffer Activates:  next gadget, topical gadget, no gadget if you select
                     an entry from the buffer listview...

- Load Buffer:       automatically: means, loading the buffer file which
                     was active on the last storing of your data file
                     automatically if you are loading this data file...


- Read/Write-Buffer: Active: Improve the speed for loading/saving.

                     First read the requester "Prefs:Read/Write-Buffer/Warning".

- Iconify:           choose AppIcon/AppItem

- Skip Field:        if you do not need a gadget from the textfield
                     select these here...

                     (Return/Enter: skip your text gadet
                      Tab:          ignore "Skip Field")
- Save
  Configuration:     Save data to  ENVARC:cdpro.prefs/tooltypes


                     ATTENTION: if there are problems with older file
                                ENVARC:cdpro.prefs, delete it.
@EndNode
@Node "buffermenu" "CDpro/Buffer menu"
@Next "export"
@Prev "Prefs"
@Toc  "Main"



- Load:                 Select a CDpro-Buffer file to load (filerequester)

- Save:                 Save buffer data to selected file (filerequester)

- Clear All Buffers:    Removes all 13 buffer lists (all buffer new)...

- Set Internal Buffers: Set some example buffer...
@EndNode
@Node "export" "CDpro/Export"
@Next "Main"
@Prev "buffermenu"
@Toc  "Main"


In advance, the data looks like printed data, apart from "List - All In One Line"
and there are no page makeups.

- Normal List:    exports the standard list,
                  limited by the menus Prefs:View/Print/Export,
                                       Prefs:Print/Export

                  for details: help requester in the menu "Print:Help"

- Topical Field:  exports topical field, see also "Normal List"

- List 0-9:       a lot of possibilities to export your data

                  for details: "Print:Describe The Lists"

- List- All In
  One Line:       export all fields you want to a single line
                  in your export file...
                  limited by the menus Prefs:View/Print/Export,
                                       Prefs:Print/Export
@EndNode
@Node "TT" "CDpro/Various:Tooltypes"
@Next "Bugs"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc  "Main"
There are 12 interesting Tooltypes. (Select CDpro program icon (tool icon) and
start "Icon:Information" from your workbench menu and change them there)...

 DATA_PATH             data path (filerequester starts with this path)

  like DATA_PATH=DH0:CDpro-Data/


 BUFFER_PATH           buffer path (filerequester starts with this path)

  like DATA_PATH=DH0:CDpro-Buffer/


 EXPORT_PATH           export path (filerequester starts with this path)

  like DATA_PATH=DH0:CDpro-Export/


 PEN                   Color for the status message and other strings.
                       Take your favourite Color (1-6)

  like PEN=6


 RWBUFFER              Size of the Read/Write-Buffer (0<=value<=1000000 Byte)

  like RWBUFFER=20480

                       Attention: use 20-100kByte, compare the RWBuffer with
                                  the size of your normal data files, the
                                  RWBuffer should`n be so much larger than
                                  these data files. (if the RWBuffer is to
                                  large the loading is not so fast...)


 PRINTER_TEST          Check the printer (offline/paperout...)
                       You can switch off this test (it is in conformity
                       with your system) if some printertools like
                       "DruckManager" have problems with it.

  like PRINTERTEST=ON or OFF


 WINDOW_X, WINDOW_Y    Window position for the next start.
                       "Save Config." also write the window position
                       to the tooltypes.

  like WINDOW_X=100 / WINDOW_Y=50


 DATA_PATTERN          Pattern for the main filename
                       (load-/save-filerequester)

  like DATA_PATTERN=#?.cdpro or DATA_PATTERN=#? (display all files)


 BUFFER_PATTERN        Pattern for the buffer filename, using for the
                       (load-/save-filerequester)

  like BUFFER_PATTERN=#?.cdbuf or BUFFER_PATTERN=#? (display all files)


 EXPORT_PATTERN        Pattern for the buffer filename, using for the
                       (load-/save-filerequester)

  like EXPORT_PATTERN=#?.cdexp or EXPORT_PATTERN=#? (display all files)


 AUTO_SAVE_PATTERN     add Patternstring (from filrequester) to filename
                       (like "name.cdpro", "name.cdexp", "name.cdbuf")

  like AUTO_SAVE_PATTERN=ON or OFF
@EndNode
@Node "Bugs" "CDpro/Various:Bugs ?"
@Next "Future"
@Prev "TT"
@Toc  "Main"
There are some incompatibilities between OS2.x und OS3.x
(special thanx to C= for it ;-) ), I hope there is no error now.

CDproV3.5 is written on 68060/OS3.0 and testet on 68000/OS2.1.

If you find a bug please send me an email as fast as possible.

 - describe the error exactly (Enforcer hits, gurus, screenshots,...)

 - system configuration you find the error (OSx.x, CPU, Screenmode...)


Special thanx.
@EndNode
